.container
  .jumbotron
    h1 Plugins
  .row
    .col-md-12
      p Socketstream has a range of plugins that you can use to build your web applications. They range from code formatters, to client-side framework extensions, and behaviour-driven development plugins.
  .row
    .col-md-12
      h2 Javascript formatters
    a(href="https://github.com/socketstream/ss-coffee")
      .col-md-3
        .thumbnail
          .caption
            h3.center ss-coffee
            p Allows you to use CoffeeScript files (.coffee) in your SocketStream project.
    a(href="https://github.com/cjam/ss-typescript")
      .col-md-3
        .thumbnail
          .caption
            h3.center ss-typescript
            p Allows you to use Typescript files (.ts) in your SocketStream project.
    a(href="https://github.com/madsflensted/ss-LiveScript")
      .col-md-3
        .thumbnail
          .caption
            h3.center ss-livescript
            p Allows you to use LiveScript files (.ls) in your SocketStream project.
    a(href="https://github.com/ckknight/ss-gorilla")
      .col-md-3
        .thumbnail
          .caption
            h3.center ss-gorilla
            p Allows you to use GorillaScript files (.gs) in your SocketStream project.
  .row
    .col-md-12
      h2 CSS formatters
    a(href="https://github.com/socketstream/ss-stylus")
      .col-md-3
        .thumbnail
          .caption
            h3.center ss-stylus
            p Allows you to use Stylus files (.styl) in your SocketStream project.
    a(href="https://github.com/socketstream/ss-less")
      .col-md-3
        .thumbnail
          .caption
            h3.center ss-less
            p Allows you to use Less files (.less) in your SocketStream project.
  .row
    .col-md-12
